title: Roundup: GW takes fourth at D-III tourney
text:
Roundup: GW takes fourth at D-III tourney Staff reports 10:40 p.m. PDT October 19, 2015 GW’s Kylie Cowell took third place at the Central Section Division III tournament. (Photo: Johanna Coyne) 31 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
The Central Grizzlies won the Central Section Division III Girls Golf Championship Monday at Valley Oaks Golf Course. 
Centrral posted a team score of 533, two shots better than second-place San Joaquin Memorial. 
Golden West led the Tulare County contingent with a fourth-place finish. The Trailblazers tied Sanger with a 555. East Yosemite League champion Tulare Western was seventh with a 588, and Dinuba was eighth with a 590. 
San Joaquin Memorial’s Maddy Laval took top individual honors with an 83. 
Golden West’s Kyle Cowell took third place with an 87. 
JC Football 
Modesto 56, COS 0: The Blue Devils crushed the Giants in Saturday’s Valley Conference opener in Modesto. 
It didn’t take long for COS (4-2, 0-1) to find out it was in for a rough game. 
Modesto (4-2, 1-0) scored on the first play from scrimmage, recovering a lost COS fumble in the end zone for a touchdown. 
The Giants finished with just 239 yards of total offense (242 passing, minus-3 rushing). Modesto compiled 539 yards of total offense (221 passing, 318 rushing). 
COS quarterback Javin Kilgo was 17-of-35 passing for 195 yards and an interception. 
COS had five turnovers (four interceptions, one lost fumble). 
Jordan Arnold (Redwood) had four catches for 78 yards, and Elijah Porchia (Mission Oak) had for receptions for 22 yards. 
COS hosts San Joaquin Delta Saturday at Giant Chevrolet-Cadillac Mineral King Bowl. Game time is 7 p.m. 
Girls Tennis 
WYL Tournament: Redwood’s Claire Yang captured the individual championship of the West Yosemite League tournament on Saturday. Yang defeated El Diamante’s Anindita Rajasekaran 6-0, 6-0 in the title match. 
Golden West’s Erica Hendrick took third place. Redwood’s Juliette Garcia and Kate Sapasap took fourth and fifth, respectively. El Diamante’s Kasandra Medina was sixth. 
All six players advance to the CIF Central Area Tournament on Oct. 30 at Redwood High School. 
The El Diamante pair of Alyssa Terry and Alyssa Thao took second place in the doubles bracket. Redwood’s duo of Allison Stevens and Mackenzie Coffman was fourth, and Redwood’s pair of Alexis Cervantes and Ashley Orandi took fifth. 
All three of those doubles teams earned a spot in the CIF Central Area Tournament. 
EYL Tournament: Mission Oak’s doubles team of Taylor Costa and Josie Gallo took third place in the East Yosemite League tournament, secruring them a spot in the CIF Central Area Tournament. Costa and Gallo posted a 6-3, 1-6, 6-2 win in the third-place match. 
Boys Water Polo 
Golden West 20, Mt. Whitney 14: The Trailblazers remained perfect in WYL action with a victory over the Pioneers at Golden West. 
Brad Dennis scored a match-best seven goals for Golden West (10-6, 7-0). Jack Felsted added five goals for the Trailblazers. Sawyer Nordell had four goals, and Brandon Green had two goals for Golden West. 
Rob Shirk paced Mt. Whitney with six goals. 
Girls Volleyball 
Farmersville 3, Orange Cove 2: The Aztecs defeated the Titans 22-25, 26-24, 14-25, 25-20, 15-12 in an East Sierra League match in Orange Cove. 
Caren Moreno and Lillian Fernandez each had eight kills for Farmersville. Jordan Castaneda added five aces. 31 CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE Read or Share this story: http://vtd-tar.co/1RTpski TOP VIDEOS
